          },
          "displayName": "ChengHuang",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
        },
        "body": "Since YARN is preparing to schedule service tasks, I think it's time for yarn to support multiple containers/processes in one raw container. AFAIK, service tasks generally have several processes in one container instance, for example, one process for the main process, one for monitoring, one for log collection, etc. \r\nHow about YARN provides some thing like POD in k8s?  \r\nWe can regard the raw YARN container as an allocation, and add SubContainer concept in ContainerLaunchContextProto. Each SubContainer can run as process or as one docker container. ",
